The paper deals with information theory and communication networks, specifically Gaussian relay and interference networks. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses network coding and optimization, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions MIMO (Multiple Input Multiple Output) networks, which is a subfield of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses coding schemes and capacities, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
